 It's obvious that we can't just outlaw the use of force in an unjust manner (a crime), so we must enumerate, outlaw, and enforce laws against the various specific things which can be used in a crime.<br>
 Rather than going down the line to include everything from guns to pointed sticks to raising your arm as if to strike a blow, we should find it easier to alter the brain and human behavior to prevent these hostile urges from being acted upon.<br>
Gun crime statistics in nations which have completely outlawed posession of firearms showing that simply outlawing them won't prevent outlaws from getting them, we should immediately begin a Manhattan Project style crash program to find the best techniques for mass population brainwashing.<br>
We should rewrite the Constitution and the Declaration of independence to say that people don't have any rights in and of themselves, unless the State is willing/able to provide for them. If the State isn't there, then it is everybody's fate to die if needed at the hands of a barbarian who slipped through the brainwashing, because it's too dangerous to let the poor little sheeple have the ability to protect themselves.<br>
