<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;It can't be repeated too often that, in the Declaration of Independence, our Founding Fathers asserted the revolutionary and &quot;self evident&quot; truth that &quot;men...are endowed by their creator with certain unalienable Rights.&quot; The Founders went on to assert, &quot;to secure these Rights, Governments are instituted among Men.&quot;<br>
