&quot;The worst threat to liberty comes not from those who simply seek their own aggrandizement, but from those who seek the good of others, identifying opposition to their desires with harm to the nation.&quot;  Richard Goodwin, address at the national board meeting of Americans for Democratic Action, 1966.<br>
